<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-05T07:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-05T07:54:00-05:00" n="958" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Legation in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shullaw</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-05T16:00:00+03:06">October 5,
                                    1943—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 6—3:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>153. Department’s 69, September 15, 11 p.m., and Legation’s 146,
                            September 26, 4 p.m.<note n="92" xml:id="d958fn92">Latter not
                                printed.</note> Request and agreement for lend-leasing of silver to
                            Saudi Arabia, signed by Bashir al Sadawi<note n="93" xml:id="d958fn93">Adviser to King Ibn Saud.</note> on October 3 <pb facs="0916" n="904" xml:id="pg_904"/> and documents together with full power
                            issued by King Ibn Saud authorizing signature delivered to Moose.</p>
                        <p>Information as to date when rials will reach Jidda and how packed.
                            Requested also form of receipt referred to in Legation’s 146 cited
                            above.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Shullaw</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>